---
By: John E. Boodin
Locus:
  Page: 347
  Verse: 8
Tags:
  - Pain
---
The pangs of pain, of failure, in this mortal lot, are the birth-throes of
transition to better things. We are separated for a time by the
indifference of space and our blindness which particularizes and isolates
us. But in us is a longing for unity.
